metadata.name: nature's beauty #1
metadata.description:
Art has been a fundamental part of human history since the beginning of time, and our earliest records show that nature, in all its shapes, forms and animals, has served humanity. 

From rocks used as hunting tools to fruit used as sustenance, humankind has always looked to nature for survival.

What is generative art?
A form of communication between the computer and you.Generative artworks also have unique characteristics because each one is produced by an algorithm - so it's not possible to make two identical pieces!
